This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring December 3, 2012, as the International Day of Persons with Disabilities. The proclamation highlights the importance of equal access and opportunity for people with disabilities and acknowledges the progress made through the Americans with Disabilities Act. It also emphasizes the need for global efforts to ensure the rights and well-being of people with disabilities worldwide. The proclamation calls on Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.